[[File:Bhujapidasana Yoga-Asana Nina-Mel.jpg|thumb|right|Bhujapidasana]]
{{Contains Indic text}}
'''Bhujapidasana ''' ({{lang-sa|भुजपीडासन}}; [[IAST]]: ''Bhujapīḍāsana'') or '''Shoulder pressing posture'''<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.yogajournal.com/poses/2498 | title = Yoga Journal - Shoulder-pressing posture | accessdate = 2012-12-07| deadurl= no}}</ref> is a [[Yoga]] [[asana]].<ref name="Iyengar2000">{{cite book | title=Light on Yoga | titlelink=Light on Yoga | publisher=Schocken | author=Iyengar, B.K.S |authorlink=B.K.S. Iyengar | year=1979 | location=New York | pages=280–2| isbn=0-8052-1031-8}}</ref>
== Etymology == The name of this asana comes from '''Bhuja''' ({{lang-sa|भुज}}) meaning "arm" or "shoulder", '''Pīḍa''' ({{lang-sa|पीडा}}) meaning "pressure" <ref name="Iyengar2000"/> and ''Asana'' ({{lang-sa|आसन}}) meaning "posture".<ref name="Sinha1996">{{cite book|last=Sinha|first=S.C.|title=Dictionary of Philosophy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-zzRvh1fRzEC&pg=PA18|accessdate=9 April 2011|date=1 June 1996|publisher=Anmol Publications PVT. LTD.|isbn=978-81-7041-293-9|page=18}}</ref>
==Description== Bhujapidasana is an arm supported [[asana]] in which the base of support are the palms of the hands. It requires both [[balance (ability)|balance]] and strength to maintain.
==See also== {{Portal|Yoga}} * [[Mālāsana]]
